<h3 id="pot" class="level2">Potentiometry (POT)
</h3>

<p class="item">
  In potentiometry, the activity of an analyte in aqueous solution is measured by a change in the potential difference E,
  <em>i.e.</em>
  the voltage between a working electrode and a reference electrode.<a href="#Tec_ref">
    <sup>[27]</sup>
  </a>
